    <string name="lbl_backup_restore_documentation_title">Backup/Restore Documentation</string>
    <string name="msg_backup_restore_documentation_content">Backup:\n
    * An SD-card is required to make a backup\n
    * All the data is included in the backup, not the preferences\n
    * The backups are placed in the SD-card directory \'worktime-backup\'\n
    * A backup file always starts with \'worktimedb-\' and ends with \'.bak\'\n
    * The combination in between is the date and time of the backup ending with 0 for an AM-time and 1 for PM\n
    * Example file-name: \'worktimedb-20111003090431-1\'
     \nRestore:\n
    * Only files in the backup directory \'worktime-backup\' on the SD-card are shown as possible restore points\n
    * If a backup is renamed and doest not start with \'worktimedb-\' AND does not end on \'.bak\' it will be ignored and not shown as possible restore point\n
    * All listed restore points are sorted by their last modified date</string>
